A COUPLE was shot and killed in the Ngxoki Administrative Area near Ngcobo in the Eastern Cape on Saturday, 18 June. According to Captain Namhla Mdleleni, it is alleged that at about 8pm, the family were in their home watching TV when two unknown men entered and fired shots at both the husband (53) and his wife (48). “They both died. A case of double murder is under investigation and police are following leads. The motive for the killing is not known at this stage,” Mdleleni said. Anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the suspects is urged to contact station commander Captain Matomane on 073 309 5022 or CrimeStop on 08600 10111. Tip-offs can be submitted on the My SAPS app.